get both the bgreenify app and donation key app of the optimisation list [at the battery section], if you have OS6 get it of the memory clean list also..  i've gotten the donation key error on a previous device [it had android 6]  you have to make sure both apps are off any "kill" and "clean" [so also whitelisted on any third party cleaner or killer or the key will fail [i even got working a few time and after a while it would stop recognising and the redirect link to the appstore donation key page]  it still might take a few installs n reinstalls to get it to work [at least on android 6] try every combo of installing [pre install key before opening greenify for the first time - dont install key app and open greenify then install trhu the link, etc etc]   on android 7 i've had no problems [took them of the optimisation list right after install and before opening either of the apps]  android 6 has bugs in the accessibillity service too and i suspect its related somehow to the donation key failing.. dunno.. im not the expert lol hope it helps..

Never manually close apps  Despite the popularity of task-killer apps for Android, manually closing running apps doesn't help battery life, a myth recently debunked by both Apple and Google. To fix either disable "Google Billing Emulation" in LP -OR- Run the Custom Patch "Support.InApp.LVL..." on the Play Store. I have paid greenify app.I achieved 100 percent battery improvement  in stock Rom rooted. I used this app with tasker. Just I did the following. Note down top battery consumer stats from OS or any battery saver app. Hibernate only the apps which is consuming power. Dont blindly hibernate all apps. Repeat until desired level of savings achieved and dont be too greedy. I have hibernated some google services and Android services without any issues which drains battery power. Be careful when touching any of the core system drivers. First they dont consume any power at all. But, by hibernating them you may get boot loop or phone become unstable. I always have auto hibernation on. Also I use tasker to execute hibernate shortcut whenever display is locked and app get released.You see battery consumption in any of the reliable battery saver app. Dont try to force install xposed framework on stock rom. It may brick your phone.

Then I discovered the Wakelock Detector app, another brilliant app, which opened my eyes to the issues... there are so many apps that keep my device out of deep sleep... THAT was the real problem... all the stuff that was happening when my device was "idle", not all the stuff that was happening when my device was "being used". Brilliant. It's a new phone. I do wonder about adding an option to regularly unfreeze select apps.  IE: Set Dropbox to unfreeze each hour, so its thing and refreeze when finished/after a few minutes.  If you were able to stagger this, you'd have somewhat regular updates of the nastier programs while still dramatically reducing load.
I didn't notice anything that the donation did, but the app is great so I'm happy to support them.

if you have android device, then you should have greenify installed! it does what it says it does +++ much more bonuses,, better battery life, better memory management, makes yr android feels brand new!
Read my opinion on the greenify app page

Getting better every week! Keep it up ;-)

This is first app that goes to any Android phone I use. So much better battery life. I can have full control over what app I want to hibernate and it restricts those notorious apps from exploiting the permissions that you gave while installing. Must have ! My appreciation to developer.
A real battery saver! Donation add-on makes it even better because then you still receive the push notifications pig hibernated apps!

This utility is obviously an experiment in a whole new way of keeping apps from running all the time, sucking up CPU cycles and eating battery charge, while still keeping them usable when you want them.  Now if this works, it will be the greatest thing since sliced bread in the Android world! :)  I paid for the "Donate" version, waited Google's 15 min and then uninstalled.  I will wait b4 using those features (need indiv enables), but I figured even if it doesn't work out, such a brilliant attempt deserves the donation and 5 Stars! :)
The free app is great and this adds great new features, but they can only be activated "all or nothing"
Surprised because such a wonderful app is not yet very popular. I just donated :)
Nice app. Improve battery life big time
Just great. Not using the pro features but what the heck, it's one of the best apps out there
Better use of xposed framework. Looking forward to continued support
I dont need the pro features, but why not donating for this awesome app and dev :) . The main app is already dominating android devices.
With the free app, I can now kill the notifications from 'social games'. I purchased the donation version to support the dev.
Excellent.. Would be better if system apps can be hibernated
This app along with juice defender have saved my sanity. Paid for app to support a great developer.
Excellent

Not sure if it's placebo effect.... and it's so hard to truly test battery life. BUT... I did get 95% deep sleep last night.  That's the first time I've seen that much deep sleep overnight on any ROM. I'm currently on 4.2.2 LiquidSmooth & 3.4 LeanKernel for d2att.

Major props on the developer for providing an incredibly useful and revolutionary app, for listening to feedback and actually implementing valid concerns and suggestions. The app doesn't push out insanely ridiculous advertisements and doesn't bug you all the time to donate. I'm donating to support the time and effort put into this and in hopes the developer will continue to improve this app. // as a suggestion myself, I can't seem to be able to greenify several apps such as Google maps which is odd
I use this daily, so seems only right to purchase. Found while surfing xda. Dev, thank you, I've seen positive results.
